list.item:
—put strong pressure on Banzer to take economic measures in his own best
                        interests, including devaluation and an IMF
                        standby;

—whether acceptance of an IMF standby should be made a condition precedent to granting any further assistance, or whether
                        standby or similar measures should be an objective which we would try to
                        achieve by using additional assistance as a lever;

—calls for the development of a phased program under which increments in
                        U.S. assistance are keyed to individual steps taken by the Banzer Government
                        in the direction of equilibrium;
